Uses of Package
org.smtlib.sexpr

  • Packages that use org.smtlib.sexpr 
    Package Description
    org.smtlib.command
    This package contains implementations of the SMT-LIB commands, implementing the interfaces defined in ICommand; these implementations are independent of the concrete syntax that might be used, except that each command object has methods that can parse or print representations of the command in the standard (or potentially other) concrete syntaxes.
    org.smtlib.ext
    This package contains commands that are extensions to SMT-LIB.
    org.smtlib.sexpr
    This package is a concrete implementation of a particular concrete syntax for the abstract SMT-LIB semantics.
    org.smtlib.solvers
    This package implements various instances of org.smtlib.ISolver, which are specific solvers that wrap and interact with various off-the-shelf SMT solvers currently available.
  • Classes in org.smtlib.sexpr used by org.smtlib.command 
    Class and Description
    Parser
    Parses the standard SMT-LIB concrete syntax to produce ASTs of objects that are instances of the org.smtlib.* interfaces.
    Printer
    This class writes out SMT-LIB ASTs as concrete S-expression syntax; aside from white space between tokens it should simply reverse what the Parser class does.

  • Classes in org.smtlib.sexpr used by org.smtlib.sexpr 
    Class and Description
    ILexToken
    An interface to indicate AST classes that are also lexical tokens in the concrete syntax.
    ISexpr
    This interface represents S-expressions as used in SMT-LIB; they are used as values for attributes in the standard concrete syntax.
    ISexpr.ISeq
    Represents a sequence of S-expressions
    ISexpr.IToken
    Represents a single S-expression token
    Lexer
    Converts character sequences (from ISource) into tokens, presuming the standard SMT-LIBv2 concrete syntax.
    Lexer.IPLexToken
    An interface used for punctuation tokens that can be retrieved from the parser input.
    Lexer.LexToken
    A lexical token class for single punctuation characters.
    Parser
    Parses the standard SMT-LIB concrete syntax to produce ASTs of objects that are instances of the org.smtlib.* interfaces.
    Sexpr
    This is the root class for S-expressions in the concrete syntax
    Sexpr.Seq
    The class corresponding to sequences of S-expressions
